10:
Um. Wouldn't it be easier to just join
one?
15:
Nephtim wants the full middle
school experience. Making one's
own club is based.
19:
It is called the "Show Club." We sing,
dance, play instruments, do magic...
Any form of performance is
authorized.
22:
We are gaining new members fast.
Our club is rapidly acquiring the "W."
25:
"Acquiring"? Er, forget it. I get what
you mean.
28:
Oh, that sounds like so much fun!
But wait... Nephtim, have you
finished your homework?
31:
You can't neglect your other
responsibilities, you know.
36:
Um... N-Nephtim has an urgent
matter to attend to. Club paperwork
requires submission.
43:
The Show Club is in session. Now
commencing club activity!
57:
Say, is it really all right for me to
join? I'm not a student, but...
62:
Access: granted. Nephtim is also a
member of FRD100. Therefore
Nephtim wants Silkhare to be in her
club too.
70:
All official members are currently
present. New members will be
included in future perform—
76:
Ah, s-sorry! Um, h-hi everyone. My
name's Kanako! Nice to meet you all!
79:
Heightened heart rate detected. Are
you experiencing a physical
abnormality?
83:
N-no, I'm fine, I... n-never mind! It
doesn't have anything to do with the
club...
86:
B-but if you really wanna know, I... I
think I kinda... started liking someone.
90:
L-like... as in love?! At long last... my
first chance at real "girl talk!"
97:
So, his name is Shinobu... He's a
grade above us, and I heard that
he's from Yamato. Know who I'm
talking about?
100:
No way—THAT guy? He's so hot! And
popular, too. Wait, doesn't he have a
girlfriend?
103:
I heard that rumor... Oh, I just hope it
isn't true! He helped me find my
classroom when I get lost, and... Ugh,
he's just so dreamy!
106:
Nephtim recognizes this scenario; it
is a common trope in manga.
Convention indicates that you
should confess your feelings to him.
108:
I mean, I know I SHOULD tell
him—and I want to! It's just... Oh god,
I'd literally die if I told him...
113:
I don't wanna make things weird! I
mean, a guy as cool as that would
never go for someone like me
anyway. Right?
114:
Plus, if he breaks up with his
girlfriend to be with me, that
wouldn't be right either!
119:
Error: paradox detected. You want to
tell him how you feel. But you also...
do not?
122:
It's like... not being able to tell him
that I like him... It makes me feel
sad... and alone.
124:
Don't get me wrong, I'm scared of
getting rejected, too. Maybe I should
just word-vomit my feelings and run
away before he can respond!
127:
...Nephtim understands what it is like
to feel scared and empty inside.
130:
Directive added: facilitate Kanako's
love confession.
133:
Do not worry. With the Show Club on
your side, love will find a way.
138:
Activating Alter Device and sound
unit.
145:
Hey yo, it's MC Nephtim, and I'm here
to impress, on you Kanako, girl, what
you gotta do is CONFESS.
148:
We're in Shi-BOOH-YEAH, it's not a
manga, hun! Just ninja sneak up on
Shinobu, steal his heart and it's
DONE!
154:
Our girl's in love! There's a man she's
dreaming of! Don't run
away—confess! You two would fit
like a GLOVE!
157:
So crush that doubt—let me hear
your heart shout! If you wanna know
the answer—just ask the boy out!
163:
No time to hesitate, let's get those
feelings out, when he hears your
love song, the man'll sing back—no
doubt!
169:
Sing it with me now!
"I love you!"
176:
Hey, you! Show Club kids! I've told
you a thousand times—you need
PERMISSION for this kind of thing!
179:
Directive: achieved. However,
teacher now looks highly irritated
and hostile.
183:
Straight Fire Mode: disengaged. The
show is over, everyone.
190:
Oof. Nephtim's big escape plan
failed.
194:
Professor Reylas' magic was sick,
though. He had me stuck inside of
that ice for real.
198:
That was sooo fun! Let's do it again!
Oh, Kanako, when are you gonna tell
that boy "I love you!" again?
201:
Actually, Shinobu asked to meet me
after our show, and... he turned me
down flat. But ergh, he looked so
freaking cool doing it!
203:
He said he doesn't have a girlfriend.
But he doesn't want one now
because his single friends would
feel left out. I don't get it AT ALL.
205:
Buuuut, now that it's all out in the
open, I feel a million times better!
Next time, let's have a huge
concert—minus the lovey-dovey
stuff!
208:
But of course! I'll help you put on the
most spectacular show this school
has ever seen!
212:
Kanako... How are your loneliness
levels? Do you feel empty inside?
215:
Hm... Most of me feels great. But to
be honest, there's still a tiny part of
me that feels sad.
217:
That's just how it is. Feelings are
complicated. I actually felt like... a
hundred times more empty inside
keeping everything bottled up.
223:
Once internal body temperatures
rise and a fuzzy feeling sets in, the
emptiness fades away. However, it
sometimes returns.
226:
That is proof that your feelings for
him were real.
229:
*sniff* Aw... Cut it out, Neph... You're
gonna make me cry! But I'm so glad
I told him. Thanks for your help.
232:
No problem. Nephtim is very mature.
Nephtim understands the
complexity of feelings.
236:
But what Nephtim wants most is to
see you smile!
